        <h1>
<a id="nashdocker" class="anchor" href="#nashdocker" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>NashDocker</h1>

<p>The Docker container mort/nashdocker makes available an IPython wrapper which replaces some of the Mathematica functions in my  monograph on algorithmic game theory: Resolving Conflicts with Mathematica, Algorithms for Two-Person Games.</p>

<p>To run it on Ubuntu Linux for example, assuming you have Docker installed, simply type</p>

<p>sudo docker run -d -p 433:8888 --name=nash mort/nashdocker</p>

<p>and point your browser to localhost:433 </p>
      </section>
